  "prompt": "What is the best site to download songs?",
  "response": "The best site to download songs can depend on your specific needs, including whether you're looking for free downloads or are willing to pay for high-quality tracks. Here are some popular options:\n\n1. **iTunes / Apple Music**: A well-known platform for purchasing and downloading songs.\n2. **Amazon Music**: Offers a wide selection of songs for purchase and download.\n3. **Google Play Music**: Although it has been replaced by YouTube Music, previously purchased songs can still be accessed through YouTube Music.\n4. **Bandcamp**: Great for discovering independent artists; many allow you to name your price for downloads.\n5. **SoundCloud**: Some artists offer free downloads of their tracks, allowing you to explore new music.\n6. **Spotify**: While primarily a streaming service, Spotify Premium allows offline listening for downloaded songs.\n\nAlways ensure you are using legal platforms to respect copyright laws and artists' rights.",
